<br>
BTW, I've had people telling me that a mage can solo PoG at 60 for cash.  Perhaps with the right equipment this is possible -- epic pet and KEI at a minimum, maybe Improved Reclaim and other AA.  For me, chaincasting 57 or 51 earth without any AA to help, the downtime was huge.<br>
<br>
In addition, I had to gate out 4 times due to adds.  The agro range on mobs is large, and bringing a mob back to your pet can often add a wanderer.  All in all, it was not a very productive 3 hours.<br>
<br>
I'm going to try this again at level 61 when I get Ward of Xegony. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A> at: 1/7/03 9:22:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wentil>Wentil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#333333>(1/7/03 2:49:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.d.umn.edu/~dander20/untitled.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG</span><hr size=1> The named horses (Galiel Swifthoof and Farstride Unicorns) see through all invis and frequently path next to the zone-in if they're up. If you don't have anyone inside watching the portal for you, the only thing you can do is cross your fingers and click the mushroom, hoping they wont be close when you zone in.<br>
<br>
All of the horses (minus Galiel) and the Gale Wolves can be solo'd by an epic mage by chan-nuking, and Glade Stalkers (black bears) and the Sanguine Kodiaks can be solo'd by a mage with 61 air and chain-nuking. The rest of the mobs I've tried have been unsuccessful, but anything might be more efficient by chain-casting, but that's not my gig. <br>
<br>
Get yourself a necro to fear or an enchanter/shaman to slow and it gets much easier. <p>Wentil Stillskin <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> Lightbringers<br>
